### Person API Testing
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api/persons

### 1. CREATE - Create a new person
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alisson Becker",
  "email": "alisson.becker@example.com",
  "alias": "alissonbecker",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 2. CREATE - Create another person
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Patrik Dorgu",
  "email": "patrik.dorgu@example.com",
  "alias": "patrikdorgu",
  "phone": "+1987654321"
}

### 3. CREATE - Create person with invalid data (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "alias": "ab",
  "phone": "123"
}

### 4. CREATE - Create person with duplicate alias (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Johnson",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "alias": "johndoe",
  "phone": "+1122334455"
}

### 5. CREATE - Create person with duplicate email (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Johnson",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "alias": "bobjohnson",
  "phone": "+1122334455"
}

### 6. GET ALL - Get all persons
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Accept: application/json

### 7. GET BY ID - Get person by ID (replace 1 with actual ID from create response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Accept: application/json

### 8. GET BY ID - Try non-existent ID (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/999
Accept: application/json

### 9. GET BY ALIAS - Get person by alias
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/alias/johndoe
Accept: application/json

### 10. GET BY ALIAS - Try non-existent alias (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/alias/nonexistent
Accept: application/json

### 11. GET BY EMAIL - Get person by email
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/email/john.doe@example.com
Accept: application/json

### 12. GET BY EMAIL - Try non-existent email (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/email/nonexistent@example.com
Accept: application/json

### 13. UPDATE - Update existing person (full update)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "alias": "johnupdated",
  "phone": "+9999999999"
}

### 14. UPDATE - Update only name (partial update)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Jr"
}

### 15. UPDATE - Update alias to existing one (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "alias": "janesmith"
}

### 16. UPDATE - Update email to existing one (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com"
}

### 17. UPDATE - Try update non-existent person (should return 404)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/persons/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost Person"
}

### 18. COUNT - Get total number of persons
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/count
Accept: application/json

### 19. DELETE - Delete person by ID
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1

### 20. DELETE - Try delete non-existent person (should return 404)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/persons/999

### 21. VERIFY DELETION - Try to get deleted person (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/1
Accept: application/json

### 22. VERIFY COUNT - Check count after deletion
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons/count
Accept: application/json

### 23. BULK CREATE - Create multiple persons for testing
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Wonderland",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "alias": "alicew",
  "phone": "+1111111111"
}

###

POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Builder",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "alias": "bobbuilder",
  "phone": "+2222222222"
}

###

POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Charlie Brown",
  "email": "charlie@example.com",
  "alias": "charlieb",
  "phone": "+3333333333"
}

### 24. GET ALL - See all created persons
GET http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Accept: application/json

### 25. TEST VALIDATION - Various invalid inputs
POST http://localhost:8080/api/persons
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "alias": "a1",
  "phone": "not-a-phone"
}